From: M28K board support
Subject: [PATCH] mmc: pwrseq_simple: only use reset controller when "resets" present

Mainline pwrseq_simple takes the reset-controller path whenever a single
reset-gpios entry is present, calling devm_reset_control_get_optional_shared().
On RK3528 boards (e.g. Widora MangoPi M28K) whose mmc-pwrseq node describes the
Wi-Fi enable purely as a GPIO (reset-gpios = wifi_reg_on) and has no "resets"
property, that call returns -EPROBE_DEFER permanently ("reset control not
ready"), so the SDIO host (sdio0) never probes and the on-board AIC8800 Wi-Fi/BT
is never powered on.

Only take the reset-controller path when the node actually has a "resets"
property; otherwise fall back to GPIO reset as before.

--- a/drivers/mmc/core/pwrseq_simple.c
+++ b/drivers/mmc/core/pwrseq_simple.c
@@ -135,7 +135,7 @@ static int mmc_pwrseq_simple_probe(struct platform_device *pdev)
 		return dev_err_probe(dev, PTR_ERR(pwrseq->ext_clk), "external clock not ready\n");

 	ngpio = of_count_phandle_with_args(dev->of_node, "reset-gpios", "#gpio-cells");
-	if (ngpio == 1) {
+	if (ngpio == 1 && of_property_present(dev->of_node, "resets")) {
 		pwrseq->reset_ctrl = devm_reset_control_get_optional_shared(dev, NULL);
 		if (IS_ERR(pwrseq->reset_ctrl))
 			return dev_err_probe(dev, PTR_ERR(pwrseq->reset_ctrl),
